00:40:30.040 --> 00:40:30.880
Were you puking?

00:40:30.960 --> 00:40:32.160
No!

00:40:33.440 --> 00:40:36.320
Oh! Mook, Mr. Pat said
that once you sober up…

00:40:37.000 --> 00:40:39.600
I mean, once you feel better,
please go see him.

00:40:58.240 --> 00:40:59.320
Come on in--

00:41:07.600 --> 00:41:08.800
All sobered up?

00:41:10.400 --> 00:41:12.080
I was starting to.

00:41:12.160 --> 00:41:14.440
Then I saw this note,
and I almost fainted.

00:41:16.080 --> 00:41:18.000
You must've drunk a whole lot.

00:41:18.080 --> 00:41:19.760
That's why you can't remember anything.

00:41:21.080 --> 00:41:22.760
At first, I didn't remember.

00:41:23.320 --> 00:41:25.960
But then I saw this,
and it all came flashing back.

00:41:29.000 --> 00:41:30.960
I wonder who I threw up on.

00:41:31.040 --> 00:41:33.400
It's fine, though. I'll handle it.

00:41:34.040 --> 00:41:36.520
You asked to see me, Boss?

00:41:45.280 --> 00:41:46.360
Is this our new client?

00:41:48.040 --> 00:41:50.360
This hotel's making its debut
here in Thailand.

00:41:51.800 --> 00:41:53.880
Their profile looks promising.

00:41:53.960 --> 00:41:56.040
If we can cut a deal with them,

00:41:56.120 --> 00:41:57.880
we'll grow our customer base by a lot.

00:41:59.400 --> 00:42:01.880
This is easy-peasy, Boss.

00:42:01.960 --> 00:42:03.840
Thought it'd be something serious.

00:42:04.760 --> 00:42:08.120
But we're up against
many other companies this time, Mook.

00:42:09.520 --> 00:42:10.920
Isn't that normal, though?

00:42:11.000 --> 00:42:12.880
We've made a ton of pitches,

00:42:12.960 --> 00:42:15.520
and you know
I always give it my all, boss.

00:42:17.800 --> 00:42:20.560
But Family Tour and Travel's one of them.

00:42:28.360 --> 00:42:29.560
You don't have to answer th--

00:42:29.640 --> 00:42:32.320
I've worked at Family Tour and Travel.

00:42:34.160 --> 00:42:36.080
And what was your position?

00:42:38.960 --> 00:42:39.960
I…

00:42:41.960 --> 00:42:43.360
co-owned the company

00:42:44.000 --> 00:42:45.520
with my husband.

00:42:49.920 --> 00:42:53.280
Mook! Mook! Mook!

00:42:53.960 --> 00:42:55.000
Wait for me.

00:42:56.000 --> 00:42:57.080
Do we know each other?

00:42:57.160 --> 00:43:00.560
You might not know me, but I know you.

00:43:00.640 --> 00:43:02.720
We're both business majors.

00:43:02.800 --> 00:43:04.200
My name's Kuk.

00:43:05.280 --> 00:43:06.560
Let's go to the cheer practice.

00:43:08.920 --> 00:43:09.920
Stop looking so confused.

00:43:10.000 --> 00:43:11.800
Quick, we gotta go before we get punished.

00:43:11.880 --> 00:43:12.880
‪Let's go.

00:43:17.440 --> 00:43:21.080
From that day on,
we were joined at the hip.

00:43:21.160 --> 00:43:24.240
Kuk's there with me,
no matter where I go or what I do.

00:43:24.760 --> 00:43:26.760
He's my very first boyfriend.

00:43:26.840 --> 00:43:30.040
Every scene I'd seen in a romantic movie,
he could replicate it.

00:43:30.640 --> 00:43:34.360
Once I started dating him,
I never had eyes for anyone else.

00:43:46.960 --> 00:43:47.920
Mook, wanna leave yet?

00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:48.920
Let's go.

00:43:49.800 --> 00:43:50.640
Ready.

00:43:52.480 --> 00:43:55.280
Yo, Kuk. Do you really
have to do all that?

00:43:55.360 --> 00:43:56.920
Don't you dare make fun of me.

00:44:09.440 --> 00:44:11.520
Did Kuk surprise you again?

00:44:11.600 --> 00:44:13.400
You're smiling like crazy.

00:44:13.480 --> 00:44:15.720
Aw! How romantic.

00:44:15.800 --> 00:44:18.040
It's hard to find
a good guy like him, Mook.

00:44:18.120 --> 00:44:19.720
He's got my vote.

00:44:21.040 --> 00:44:23.000
He's said a couple times

00:44:23.080 --> 00:44:25.760
that he wants me to meet his mom and…

00:44:26.280 --> 00:44:28.200
that we should get married.

00:44:29.480 --> 00:44:30.320
- Married?
- Married?

00:44:34.880 --> 00:44:35.800
Oh my!

00:44:37.400 --> 00:44:39.920
What, Master? Is something wrong?

00:44:40.800 --> 00:44:44.320
Your son's the reincarnation of a dragon!

00:44:44.400 --> 00:44:46.680
He's truly a rare find!

00:44:47.440 --> 00:44:49.000
At the time of his birth,

00:44:49.080 --> 00:44:51.160
Saturn was opposing Mercury.

00:44:51.240 --> 00:44:53.960
This alignment is fixed in his star sign.

00:44:54.880 --> 00:44:57.160
He's diligent,

00:44:57.240 --> 00:45:00.480
hardworking, and clever.

00:45:00.560 --> 00:45:02.520
He's a leader as well.

00:45:03.400 --> 00:45:06.000
He was born at exactly the right time!

00:45:06.600 --> 00:45:09.520
He's the dragon of dragons!

00:45:10.040 --> 00:45:12.120
He's rich, wealthy,

00:45:12.200 --> 00:45:14.760
and he was born to be superior!

00:45:16.120 --> 00:45:17.680
You’re spot on!

00:45:17.760 --> 00:45:19.760
Everything you said is right.

00:45:19.840 --> 00:45:21.080
Since the day he was born,

00:45:21.160 --> 00:45:24.720
money came pouring in,
and everyone lived happily.

00:45:26.960 --> 00:45:30.040
But Ma, didn't Pa die when I was born?

00:45:33.840 --> 00:45:35.440
That's got nothing to do with it.

00:45:35.520 --> 00:45:37.760
Your Pa was already badly ill.

00:45:40.680 --> 00:45:43.680
Uh… Yeah! You see,

00:45:43.760 --> 00:45:47.160
that's when the moon parted
and sent for the sun

00:45:47.240 --> 00:45:49.160
to take its place, young man.

00:45:55.320 --> 00:45:59.080
Ma, what about Mook? How's her star sign?

00:45:59.160 --> 00:46:01.640
- Is she my soulmate?
- Yeah, check her star sign.

00:46:01.720 --> 00:46:04.560
- Check Mook's star sign.
- Oh, Mook's? Sure.

00:46:04.640 --> 00:46:07.000
Just a second. Let me analyze first.

00:46:32.360 --> 00:46:34.040
Is Kongkwan asleep, honey?

00:46:34.120 --> 00:46:36.880
Yes, Mom. She slept a while ago.

00:46:41.640 --> 00:46:42.960
How are you?

00:46:43.800 --> 00:46:46.960
Has work been tough? You look tense.

00:46:47.480 --> 00:46:48.840
Is something wrong?

00:47:00.080 --> 00:47:00.920
Mom.

00:47:03.200 --> 00:47:06.400
When I told you
I was going to get married,

00:47:07.240 --> 00:47:08.920
how'd you feel?

00:47:12.760 --> 00:47:15.960
Sorry I asked you
to come all the way here to talk.

00:47:16.960 --> 00:47:21.120
Kuk told me your house is so so far away.

00:47:22.480 --> 00:47:26.760
I just don't feel comfortable
traveling so so far away.

00:47:26.840 --> 00:47:28.000
I just can't.

00:47:29.800 --> 00:47:32.400
That's alright. I understand.

00:47:33.160 --> 00:47:34.920
Shall we start talking?

00:47:38.440 --> 00:47:40.720
Well, it's about their marriage.

00:47:40.800 --> 00:47:44.280
My son wants to marry your daughter,

00:47:44.360 --> 00:47:47.480
so I wanted him to ask you
for her hand in marriage.

00:47:50.640 --> 00:47:54.120
But I want Mook to change
her first and last name first.

00:47:55.440 --> 00:47:57.480
Why do I have to do that?

00:47:57.560 --> 00:47:59.520
'Cause it's bad luck, of course!

00:47:59.600 --> 00:48:02.120
Your marriage wouldn’t last.

00:48:02.200 --> 00:48:04.160
You'd only cause our downfall.

00:48:04.240 --> 00:48:07.000
Then my son’s life will be ruined too.

00:48:10.960 --> 00:48:11.800
I won't change it.

00:48:13.320 --> 00:48:16.120
I’m proud of the name my parents gave me.

00:48:16.640 --> 00:48:20.280
If he won't marry me
just because of this, then so be it.

00:48:22.560 --> 00:48:24.560
Mom, let's go home.

00:48:24.640 --> 00:48:27.000
Mook, Mook! Please calm down.

00:48:27.080 --> 00:48:29.240
Don't be mad. Please, Mook.

00:48:32.960 --> 00:48:34.640
Ma!

00:48:36.160 --> 00:48:37.960
Please, I insist.

00:48:38.040 --> 00:48:39.800
I only want to marry her.

00:48:39.880 --> 00:48:43.720
If you don't let me,
I won't marry anyone ever.

00:48:47.720 --> 00:48:50.520
I love you, Mook.

00:48:51.400 --> 00:48:52.520
I'd run away with you

00:48:52.600 --> 00:48:55.240
because I can't live without you.

00:48:55.320 --> 00:48:57.360
Please don't leave me, Mook.

00:48:58.080 --> 00:48:59.240
Please, Mook…

00:49:00.040 --> 00:49:00.880
Please!

00:49:00.960 --> 00:49:04.760
Okay, okay!
You don't have to change it then.

00:49:06.320 --> 00:49:07.200
Ma!

00:49:08.640 --> 00:49:10.400
Silly boy…

00:49:14.200 --> 00:49:15.960
Thank you, Ma!

00:49:21.120 --> 00:49:22.280
Ah-ma!

00:49:23.960 --> 00:49:27.080
- Thank you for coming.
- Of course!

00:49:27.160 --> 00:49:29.720
Thank you. Kuk, take her to her seat.

00:49:29.800 --> 00:49:32.160
- Sure. This way, Ah-ma.
- Careful.

00:49:32.240 --> 00:49:33.840
Easy, Ah-ma.

00:49:33.920 --> 00:49:35.720
Thank you.

00:49:36.760 --> 00:49:38.880
- Right, Ah-ma.
- So you've brought…

00:49:38.960 --> 00:49:40.400
- This is Mook's mother.
- Ah-ma too.

00:49:40.480 --> 00:49:43.160
- You shut down the factory for the day?
- Yeah.

00:49:43.240 --> 00:49:44.520
Please take a seat.

00:49:44.600 --> 00:49:48.120
Thank you. I'm glad you made it today.

00:49:50.000 --> 00:49:52.040
And how's business going?

00:49:53.160 --> 00:49:54.960
- Looking great today!
- Thank you.

00:49:57.240 --> 00:50:01.000
Thank you for understanding
and letting me host such a…

00:50:01.080 --> 00:50:03.400
cozy little wedding.

00:50:04.160 --> 00:50:07.000
The wedding's just a ceremony.

00:50:07.080 --> 00:50:09.160
Our kids love each other.

00:50:09.240 --> 00:50:12.280
That's what matters most. Don't you think?

00:50:13.400 --> 00:50:15.400
Please take good care of Mook.

00:50:15.480 --> 00:50:18.000
It's always been just us two.

00:50:18.640 --> 00:50:20.040
Whoever she loves,

00:50:20.840 --> 00:50:22.160
I'll love them too.

00:50:26.960 --> 00:50:28.640
Thank you for coming.

00:50:28.720 --> 00:50:31.000
You left the factory behind
just to come here, right?

00:50:33.200 --> 00:50:35.680
Of course! We need you here!

00:50:38.160 --> 00:50:41.440
Thank you for having me.
I've seen Kuk since he was little.

00:50:43.320 --> 00:50:46.280
Is this a wedding or a meditation center?

00:50:46.360 --> 00:50:49.760
It's so quiet I could count
the guests on one hand!

00:50:49.840 --> 00:50:51.240
I'd be furious if I were you.

00:50:51.320 --> 00:50:53.160
Why be so stingy over a wedding?

00:50:53.240 --> 00:50:55.360
For God's sake…

00:50:55.440 --> 00:50:59.560
Can you stand being a cliché wife
with a mother-in-law like her, Mook?

00:51:00.280 --> 00:51:02.080
Enough, Khim.

00:51:02.160 --> 00:51:03.840
Sometimes,

00:51:03.920 --> 00:51:07.040
the wedding doesn't matter
as much as the love.

00:51:07.120 --> 00:51:08.560
Just say they're stingy.

00:51:09.440 --> 00:51:11.480
Why'd you stand for all this, Mook?

00:51:13.400 --> 00:51:15.280
It's what I get for not changing my name.

00:51:16.640 --> 00:51:19.880
Kuk's mom is very superstitious.

00:51:20.440 --> 00:51:23.120
That's why I had to meet her halfway

00:51:23.200 --> 00:51:25.600
and have a quiet wedding
to prevent bad luck.

00:51:29.040 --> 00:51:31.760
I just can't imagine
the things you'll have to face.

00:51:33.600 --> 00:51:34.840
Don't worry.

00:51:34.920 --> 00:51:38.880
Once you get married,
maybe things will be better.

00:51:39.480 --> 00:51:43.680
These days, there shouldn't be any
cliché mother-in-laws like in TV soaps.

00:51:45.360 --> 00:51:48.240
Either way, I'm happy for you, Mook.

00:51:48.320 --> 00:51:50.760
I hope you'll be very happy.

00:51:51.560 --> 00:51:52.720
Thank you.

00:51:54.640 --> 00:51:58.360
You must really love Kuk
to put up with all this.

00:52:10.320 --> 00:52:12.440
I wish you…

00:52:13.280 --> 00:52:15.320
happiness in your marriage.

00:52:23.400 --> 00:52:25.720
Thank you so much, you two.

00:52:33.360 --> 00:52:34.640
FAMILY

00:52:46.000 --> 00:52:48.840
If getting married is like going to war,

00:52:48.920 --> 00:52:51.760
then I already stepped
into the battlefield that day.

00:52:52.800 --> 00:52:54.480
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

00:52:54.560 --> 00:52:56.960
Novels aren't made
of just a hero and a heroine.

00:52:57.040 --> 00:53:00.280
The mother-in-law
is a main character in every story.

00:53:01.360 --> 00:53:04.560
Wakey-wakey! Rise and shine, honey!

00:53:05.680 --> 00:53:08.160
Kuk, time to get up!

00:53:10.760 --> 00:53:14.680
Kuk, get up and have some bird's nest.
Come on, honey.

00:53:14.760 --> 00:53:16.520
- Ma?
- Come on, sweetheart.

00:53:16.600 --> 00:53:20.520
Quick, while it's hot.

00:53:22.400 --> 00:53:25.080
I'm all grown now, Ma.

00:53:25.160 --> 00:53:26.440
You don't have to feed me.

00:53:28.600 --> 00:53:31.000
You're still my son,
no matter how old you get.

00:53:32.800 --> 00:53:34.880
Come on.

00:53:35.760 --> 00:53:40.440
Open wide… Good boy!

00:53:40.520 --> 00:53:42.440
Good morning, Ma.

00:53:44.080 --> 00:53:45.200
Dear me!

00:53:45.280 --> 00:53:47.960
I forgot my son's got a wife now.

00:53:49.120 --> 00:53:53.520
Normally, I have to get up early
to cook and take care of him.

00:53:53.600 --> 00:53:55.240
I got too used to it.

00:53:56.040 --> 00:53:59.680
Now that he has a wife,
it should be the wife's job, then.

00:54:00.760 --> 00:54:01.800
Of course, Ma.

00:54:01.880 --> 00:54:03.920
From now on, I'll take care of him.

00:54:05.280 --> 00:54:07.640
You have to go greet your family today,

00:54:07.720 --> 00:54:09.640
since some of them
couldn't come to the wedding.

00:54:09.720 --> 00:54:11.480
Go shower and get dressed, son.

00:54:11.560 --> 00:54:13.640
I'll wait downstairs.

00:54:17.800 --> 00:54:20.960
You don't have to go. You should stay
and take care of the house.

00:54:21.040 --> 00:54:23.400
There's lots of laundry to do.

00:54:23.480 --> 00:54:25.680
Just so many chores.

00:54:25.760 --> 00:54:27.880
You see, our maid is away on leave.

00:54:27.960 --> 00:54:29.640
Can I leave it to you?

00:54:30.760 --> 00:54:31.960
Sure, Ma.

00:54:36.680 --> 00:54:38.320
I'd better go shower then.

00:54:42.040 --> 00:54:43.400
Wanna come with us, Mook?

00:54:44.120 --> 00:54:45.320
I'll go tell Ma.

00:54:45.840 --> 00:54:49.640
Uh… It's okay, Kuk. Just go with your ma.

00:54:49.720 --> 00:54:51.720
I've got some work to do too.

00:54:53.920 --> 00:54:56.080
Go on. Don't keep her waiting.

00:55:31.040 --> 00:55:34.320
"Please do the laundry,
iron, clean the kitchen,

00:55:34.400 --> 00:55:36.240
and clean the house for me, Mook.

00:55:36.880 --> 00:55:38.320
Thank you."

00:56:05.240 --> 00:56:06.080
{\an8}That's enough.

00:56:06.160 --> 00:56:08.880
{\an8}- Fire! Help! There's a fire!
- Huh? A fire?!

00:56:08.960 --> 00:56:10.280
{\an8}- Fire!
- Fire?!

00:56:10.360 --> 00:56:13.320
{\an8}Where's the fire? Where?

00:56:13.400 --> 00:56:15.120
{\an8}Quitting just 'cause you're losing?

00:56:15.200 --> 00:56:17.680
{\an8}No way!
Get back here and finish the round!

00:56:17.760 --> 00:56:19.840
{\an8}I'm on a roll, you know.

00:56:19.920 --> 00:56:23.200
{\an8}Ma, don't keep your guests waiting.

00:56:34.520 --> 00:56:35.840
{\an8}Don't worry, Boss.

00:56:35.920 --> 00:56:37.480
{\an8}Just stand still and relax.

00:56:40.360 --> 00:56:42.200
{\an8}I'll finish in just a second.

00:56:44.040 --> 00:56:46.840
{\an8}I do this all the time.
Just trust my hands, okay?

00:57:38.280 --> 00:57:40.560
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya